title: Microsoft Azure Status
agents: azure_status
catalog: cloud/azure
license: GPLv2
distribution: check_mk
description:
 This check reports the issues on Microsoft Azure infrastructure
 from https://azure.status.microsoft/en-us/status/.

 To make this check work you have to configure the related special
 agent {Microsoft Azure Status}. The regions, which are discovered,
 can be configured.

 Importantly, since this check is based on the public health dashboard, there
 are more accurate ways to monitor Azure. If you can, choose the {Microsoft
 Azure} monitoring over this monitoring solution.

item:
 The name of the region.

discovery:
 One service is created for each region.
 Additionally, one service is created for global Azure services.
